<br>
This is only my second rod but since i am in oasis hunting i figured i would get it while i am here<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uyahtzooba.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yahtzooba</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/01 9:26 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Staff of the wheel Oasis Rod</span><hr size=1>  Standing on the shore with the inn at your back and to the right, you can walk into the water and see the tower. Invis and swim out to above the tower and slowly drift down until you spot the rod (can be hard to see), snag it and swim away. I was quite surprised that they did not jump me with simple invis on, very scary moment, very satisfying results...  go get yer rod! /cheer  Yaht, 24th cannon <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukilamyan00.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kilamyan 00</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/19/01 2:18 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Staff of the wheel Oasis Rod</span><hr size=1> Get wolf form from a druid. Don't use invis.  You become Apprehensive to all of the DWGobs with Wolf Form.<br>
<br>
-Kila <p>.................
[image]www.easydynamics.com/eq/Cat.jpg[/image]</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uyahtzooba.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yahtzooba</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/19/01 9:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Staff of the wheel Oasis Rod</span><hr size=1>  Apprehensive with wolfform, or indifferent with invis. Your choice... think I'd rather have indiff.<br>
 Yaht <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uorsmoxlorr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Orsmo Xlorr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/01 11:02 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> oasis rod</span><hr size=1> NO.  That tower you see with the spectre's is not the tower you want.  The tower you are looking for is under the water.  You will notice how the  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulordbug.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LordBug</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 124<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/01 3:08 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: oasis rod</span><hr size=1> Just use invis and come in from above.  Pick up the rod (left-click, not right) and swim to shore.  Bag it on shore.  Mission accomplished, 30 seconds max. <p><BR><BR>
