<br>
Wolf for IS Ideal.  Here is why.<br>
<br>
1: Indiff or Appre, either way they aren't attacking<br>
<br>
2: Wolf form has a more or less defined duration<br>
<br>
3: The Gobs *sometimes* see invis<br>
<br>
This applies for both the Lake Rathe, and the Oasis rod.<br>
<br>
<br>
In Oasis they saw invis my first trip.  I spoke to another wizard who was in progress, and he said they didn't.<br>
<br>
I went back a day or two later, and they didn't see it.  Grabbed the rod, it is tough to see.<br>
<br>
-<br>
Same situation in Rathe.  2 visits.  First no wolf form.  The gob in the tower saw invis, but the rest didn't.<br>
<br>
Second trip, guild wedding right above it at the aviaks.  Got Wolf, endure, invis for good measure.  Swam in, they conned indif (didn't see invis).  Got my rod.  Invis dropped as I was swimming away, but they were still apprehensive.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Hope this helps,<br>
Iudar Stoneburner<br>
<br>
<br>
