<br>
I'm on prexus if you send me a tell i will gladly help you out.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uiudar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iudar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/22/01 5:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> L Guk rod</span><hr size=1> I have accually yet to make the attempt.  I'm hoping to bring the 2 high lvl guild necros with me for backup.  One is a friend, one owes me a favor.<br>
<br>
The problem is I don't know L Guk at all, and have only been to Upper Guk once.<br>
<br>
I'd be grateful beyond words for someone to look at the EQAtlas maps for U and L Guk, and post the approx loc of which zone I should use.  I should be ok from there.<br>
<br>
<br>
I do intend to do this on either a friday or saturday night.  Make things as easy as possible.<br>
<br>
I'm on Torvonnilous, if there is anyone there that can help me, I'm sure I can find a way to show my gratitude.<br>
<br>
Thanks again <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulummanaburn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LumManaburn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/23/01 11:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: L Guk rod</span><hr size=1> The goblins in Oasis saw thru my invis when I grabbed the rod. Was able to make the shoreline before dieing. The LR goblins did not see my invis. Hope this helps.<br>
<br>
The Hand was camped when I tried for the Lguk rod. I just waited with the group that was camping the Hand (and all of its friends) to pull it. It was a quick run to the room, got the rod and then gated out. At the time I did have Invis to Undead so getting there was fairly easy. That is if you call running by a ton of nasty undead frogloks easy. If you dont have ITU or are not high enough for that spell, bring a friend that has it. Paly, Necro, SK, Enchanter and Clerics all can help you get there. Or you can buy ITU potions.<br>
<br>
The Lguk rod was the last rod I needed to complete the quest. In all I died twice, Oasis and my first trip to Lguk when I got killed in the BR by a train. Looking back I wish I had worked on the quest when I was lower level (started at 35, finished at 40).  In all, it was perhaps the best quest I have ever done both by the challenge and reward.   <p><center>
